Rapper and composer Tshifhiwa Sigaima, well known as Lirroy, released his first album, The golden rule II, on 5 May. The album has 12 tracks and includes popular tracks such as Pineapple, Marandela, Aunty and Days of joy. Lirroy said his album was about the rules of life that every living being must abide by. "In life we live by rules - whether in love or in careers, there are rules and this album talks about those golden rules," he said. The young rapper from Ha-Rabali in Nzhelele said that music to him was like an imaginary friend that never left his side and was always with him through trials and tribulations. "I love music and I love making music. I live to make music." 